description:
Introduce the execution substrate type abstraction that all subsequent work depends on.

## Current State (what exists today)

In `packages/pi-beadwork-extension/src/types.ts`, `WorkerRuntime` is a flat object type with `branchName: string` and `worktreePath: string` as required top-level fields. There are ~53 references to `.worktreePath` across 10 files and ~11 references to `.branchName` across 5 files.

## What to implement

### New types in `types.ts`:

```ts
export type WorkerExecutionMode = "current-branch" | "worktree";

export type CurrentBranchCheckout = {
  executionMode: "current-branch";
  checkoutPath: string;    // repo root / current checkout
  branchName: string;      // branch recorded at launch
  launchHead: string;      // required: attribution search starts here
};

export type WorktreeCheckout = {
  executionMode: "worktree";
  checkoutPath: string;    // worker worktree path (= worktreePath)
  branchName: string;
  worktreePath: string;    // kept for worktree-specific code
};

export type WorkerCheckout = CurrentBranchCheckout | WorktreeCheckout;
```

### Restructure `WorkerRuntime`:

```ts
// Extract all non-checkout fields into a base type
export type BaseWorkerRuntime = {
  workerId: string;
  ticketId: string;
  epicId?: string;
  ticketTitle: string;
  ticketStatus?: string;
  backend: "tmux";
  tmuxSession: string;
  tmuxWindow: string;
  tmuxPane: string;
  runtimeDir: string;
  promptFile: string;
  scriptFile: string;
  logFile: string;
  stateFile: string;
  exitCodeFile: string;
  finishedAtFile: string;
  launchCommand: string;
  workerCommand: string;
  workerProvider?: string;
  workerModel?: string;
  cleanupPolicy?: BeadworkConfig["worktrees"]["cleanup"]; // legacy/worktree-only; current-branch records must not populate/use this
  // ... all other existing non-checkout fields ...
  status: WorkerStatus;
  startedAt: string;
  updatedAt: string;
  finishedAt?: string;
  lastError?: string;
  // Verification results (populated during Phase 3)
  commitShas?: string[];
  touchedPaths?: string[];
};

export type WorkerRuntime = BaseWorkerRuntime & WorkerCheckout;
```

### Type guards:

```ts
export function isCurrentBranchWorker(w: WorkerRuntime): w is BaseWorkerRuntime & CurrentBranchCheckout {
  return w.executionMode === "current-branch";
}
export function isWorktreeWorker(w: WorkerRuntime): w is BaseWorkerRuntime & WorktreeCheckout {
  return w.executionMode === "worktree";
}
```

## Migration Strategy for Existing Code

Most `.worktreePath` references are in worktree-specific functions that will only ever receive worktree workers:

1. **`worktree.ts` (17 refs)** — Functions like `prepareTicketWorktree`, `rebaseWorktreeOntoRepoHead`, `landWorktreeBranch` already only handle worktrees. Give them a narrowed parameter type: `worker: BaseWorkerRuntime & WorktreeCheckout`. All internal `.worktreePath` references compile without guards.

2. **`orchestrator.ts` (22 refs)** — Most are inside worktree-specific functions (`autoLandCompletedWorker`, `gatherReviewArtifacts`, `runWorktreeValidation`, etc.). Give those narrowed parameter types. The 5-10 TOP-LEVEL dispatch points (like `inspectWorkerRuntime`) need `if (isWorktreeWorker(worker))` guards.

3. **`registry.ts` (2 refs)** — Registry serialization writes whatever fields exist. Use `as WorkerRuntime` when reading, with normalization (task .1.4) ensuring all records have `executionMode`.

4. **Remaining files (5 refs)** — `handoff.ts`, `tui/worker-manager.ts`, `actions/delegate.ts`, `actions/cleanup.ts`, `tmux.ts` — small focused changes.

5. **Test files (7 refs)** — Update fixtures to include `executionMode: "worktree"` and `checkoutPath`.

## Design Rules

- `executionMode` is THE discriminant — use it in all type narrowing
- `worktreePath` only exists on `WorktreeCheckout` — do NOT include it as optional on `CurrentBranchCheckout`
- `launchHead` is required on `CurrentBranchCheckout` — it must always be recorded at launch
- Current-branch workers must NOT fake `worktreePath = repoRoot`
- Worktree cleanup fields/policies are legacy/worktree-only; current-branch runtime records must not populate `cleanupPolicy` from `worktrees.cleanup`, and current-branch orchestration must never consult it
- Both checkout shapes have `branchName` (accessible without narrowing)
- Both checkout shapes have `checkoutPath` (accessible without narrowing)
- `commitShas` and `touchedPaths` are optional on base (populated in Phase 3)
- Worktree-specific functions take narrowed parameter types to avoid guards inside their bodies
- TypeScript strict mode will find every missed callsite — that's the point

## Tests

- Type guard correctness with both checkout shapes
- Compile-time impossible-state tests (accessing `worktreePath` on current-branch should be type error)
- Serialization/deserialization round-trip for both shapes
- `commitShas` and `touchedPaths` optional fields serialize correctly when present/absent
- Test fixtures updated and compiling
- `branchName` and `checkoutPath` accessible without narrowing (both shapes)
- Current-branch runtime fixtures omit worktree-only cleanup fields; worktree fixtures preserve `cleanupPolicy` for backward compatibility

## Definition of Done

- Types compile cleanly with strict TypeScript
- ALL existing code compiles with the new type (type narrowing applied where needed)
- Type guards exported and tested
- Existing tests pass (may need fixture updates to include `executionMode`)
- lint/test/typecheck pass clean
